  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Facilities Manager (East)",
  "description": "<p>Job Scope:</p><ul><li>Oversee and plan operational and preventive maintenance activities.</li><li><p>Manage and evaluate vendor performance in accordance with service agreements.</p></li><li><p>Lead and supervise engineers, technicians, and contractors for daily building operations and maintenance.</p></li><li><p>Review, recommend, and implement work order variations within delegated authority.</p></li><li><p>Monitor preventive maintenance schedules, fault reports, and corrective work orders.</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with all safety regulations and statutory requirements.</p></li><li><p>Manage A&A works, repairs, redecorations, and other project-related activities.</p></li><li><p>Supervise on-site teams and handle staff management matters.</p></li><li><p>Foster strong working relationships with team members and building owners.</p></li><li><p>Prepare and present weekly service/maintenance reports and monthly management reports.</p></li></ul><p>Requirements:</p><ul><li>Degree in Engineering, Building/ Facilities Management or equivalent.</li><li>Minimum 8 years of relevant work experiences.</li></ul><p>Interested applicants are welcome to submit your MS Word resume to career@oneconsulting-global.com</p><p><br />EA Personnel: R1107675<br />Agency No.: 07C3676</p>",
